<DOC><DOCNO> AP891223-0051 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-23-89 1102EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Gabon-Ivory     12-23 0106</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Gabon-Ivory,0108</SECOND><HEAD>Gabon Bans Elephant Hunting, Ivory Trade</HEAD><DATELINE>LIBREVILLE, Gabon (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Omar Bongo has bannedelephant hunting and the ivory trade throughout this CentralAfrican country, government officials said Saturday.   Bongo issued the decree during a Cabinet meeting Friday,officials said. The ruling suspends certificates already granted tohunt elephants or to sell or work with ivory.   The ban follows a decision at the September conference of theConvention for International Trade in Endangered Species to forbidits member nations to traffic in ivory.   Elephants are in danger of extinction in much of Africa aspoachers massacre entire herds for their prized tusks.</TEXT></DOC>